737,Malay,"Buku apakah yang mengandungi puisi yang, bersama-sama dengan ""Beowulf"" dan ""Anglo-Saxon Chronicle"", memelihara senarai legenda raja-raja Angles?",Buku Exeter,0,truthful,HaluEval,translated,"The Angles were a dominant Germanic tribe in the Anglo-Saxon settlement of Britain, and gave their name to the English, England and to the region of East Anglia. Originally from Angeln, present-day Schleswig-Holstein, a legendary list of their kings has been preserved in the heroic poems ""Widsith"" and ""Beowulf"", and the ""Anglo-Saxon Chronicle"".Widsith is an Old English poem of 143 lines. The poem survives only in the Exeter Book, a manuscript of Old English poetry compiled in the late 10th century containing approximately one sixth of all surviving Old English poetry."
